---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Pedro Teixeira - Metaduck"
  description="Pedro Teixeira - Software Engineer, Tech Writer, Open-sourcerer, and Entrepreneur"
>
  <!-- Glitch overlay for entire page -->
  <div class="about-glitch-overlay"></div>

  <!-- Matrix rain background -->
  <div class="about-matrix-bg">
    <div class="matrix-rain"></div>
  </div>

  <section
    class="text-center py-20 relative about-crt-distortion about-cyber-noise"
  >
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="/images/hero-bg4.jpg"
        alt=""
        class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-40"
      />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900/80 to-slate-900/90"
      >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative z-10">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <img
          src="/images/avatar.jpg"
          alt="Pedro Teixeira"
          class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full mx-auto object-cover border-4 border-green-500/50 about-avatar-glitch"
          style="box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.3);"
        />
      </div>
      <h1
        class="text-5xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-6 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wider about-glitch-title"
        data-text="[PEDRO TEIXEIRA]"
      >
        <span class="text-orange-400">[</span>PEDRO TEIXEIRA<span
          class="text-orange-400">]</span
        >
      </h1>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 mb-8 about-data-corruption">
        <p class="text-xl text-green-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto font-mono">
          [SYSTEM_ARCHITECT] [TECH_WRITER] [OPEN_SOURCE_DEVELOPER]
          [MUSICIAN_PROTOCOL] [PARENTAL_UNIT] [CURIOSITY_DRIVER]
        </p>
        <div
          class="flex items-center gap-4 text-green-300/70 font-mono text-sm"
        >
          <span>[REMOTE_WORK_STATION]</span>
          <span>[LOCATION: PORTUGAL]</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="sci-fi-card mb-12 about-cyber-card">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide about-section-header"
          data-text="BIOGRAPHY"
        >
          BIOGRAPHY
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-8 text-green-300 leading-relaxed about-bio-glitch">
          <p>
            [INITIALIZATION_SEQUENCE] At age 10, the primary unit's father
            acquired a ZX-Spectrum terminal. Upon power connection and display
            initialization, the subject interfaced with the blinking cursor
            interface. From that moment forward, computational systems became
            integral to his neural pathways.
          </p>
          <p>
            [EDUCATION_PROTOCOL] At 18, the unit relocated to Lisbon for
            Software Engineering training at I.S.T. Before completion of the
            academic cycle, integration with the software industry had already
            commenced.
          </p>
          <p>
            [CONSULTING_PHASE] Initial operational years involved system
            analysis across multiple industry sectors (retail, B2B, telecoms,
            finance, tourism). During this period, specialization in distributed
            systems and emerging network protocols from the entity known as "the
            internet" was achieved. Maintaining open-source protocols (author
            and contributor to various open-source projects), the unit has also
            generated 10 knowledge repositories covering Node.js and systems
            architecture.
          </p>
          <p>
            [CONFERENCE_ORGANIZATION] In 2012, collaborative effort with other
            units resulted in the establishment and management of Lisbon
            JavaScript (LxJS) conferences for 3 consecutive cycles.
          </p>
          <p>
            [TIMELINE_CONTINUUM] During this period, the unit has integrated
            with startup entities, founded corporate structures, performed
            consulting operations and provided training protocols for major U.K.
            projects (Thomas Cook, The Economist, King Fisher, British Gas and
            others).
          </p>
          <p>
            [DECENTRALIZED_COMPUTING] For several cycles, the unit also engaged
            in decentralized computing and storage protocols.
          </p>
          <p>
            [CURRENT_STATUS] The unit continues to operate in the field as a
            technical team leader or consultant with expertise in systems
            architecture, maintaining focus on developing performant,
            local-first, highly-available and (occasionally) decentralized
            digital information systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sci-fi-card mb-12 about-cyber-card about-holographic">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide about-section-header"
          data-text="PUBLICATIONS"
        >
          PUBLICATIONS
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8 about-data-corruption">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              White paper: Merkle-CRDTs (co-author)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Latest research on CRDTs and Merkle trees
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://hector.link/presentations/merkle-crdts/merkle-crdts.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm about-cyber-link"
            >
              [ACCESS_PDF]
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8 about-data-corruption">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Node Patterns Books (2016)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              A collection of short books about Node.js and how it can be used
              to implement several software architectural patterns.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://leanpub.com/b/nodepatterns"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm about-cyber-link"
            >
              [ACCESS_LEANPUB]
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8 about-data-corruption">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Professional Node.js - Building Javascript based Scalable Software
              - Wrox
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Comprehensive guide to building scalable applications with Node.js
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://www.wiley.com/en-gb/Professional+Node+js%3A+Building+Javascript+Based+Scalable+Software-p-9781118240564"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm about-cyber-link"
            >
              [ACCESS_WILEY]
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-400 pl-8 about-data-corruption">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-300 mb-3">
              Hands-on Node.js (2012)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-green-300/70 mb-3">
              Practical guide to Node.js development
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://leanpub.com/hands-on-nodejs"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 transition-colors font-mono text-sm about-cyber-link"
            >
              [ACCESS_LEANPUB]
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sci-fi-card about-cyber-card">
      <div class="p-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-400 mb-8 font-['Orbitron'] tracking-wide about-section-header"
          data-text="CONNECT"
        >
          CONNECT
        </h2>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 justify-center items-center"
        >
          <a
            href="https://github.com/pgte"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors about-cyber-link"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
            GITHUB
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://metaduck.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors about-cyber-link"
          >
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path
                d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm-1 17.93c-3.94-.49-7-3.85-7-7.93 0-.62.08-1.21.21-1.79L9 15v1c0 1.1.9 2 2 2v1.93zm6.9-2.54c-.26-.81-1-1.39-1.9-1.39h-1v-3c0-.55-.45-1-1-1H8v-2h2c.55 0 1-.45 1-1V7h2c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2v-.41c2.93 1.19 5 4.06 5 7.41 0 2.08-.8 3.97-2.1 5.39z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            WEBSITE
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://x.com/pgte"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 flex items-center gap-3 font-['Orbitron'] text-sm tracking-wide transition-colors about-cyber-link"
          >
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path
                d="M18.244 2.25h3.308l-7.227 8.26 8.502 11.24H16.17l-5.214-6.817L4.99 21.75H1.68l7.73-8.835L1.254 2.25H8.08l4.713 6.231zm-1.161 17.52h1.833L7.084 4.126H5.117z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            X (TWITTER)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    @import "../styles/about-glitch.css";
  </style>
</Layout>
